{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Commission a review into racial inequalities in the criminal justice system",
        "additional_details": "We urge the Government to review issues of racial disparity rates in relation to stop and search, arrest, prosecution and sentencing.\r\n \r\nBlack people are four times as likely to be in prison than white people.\r\n \r\nDramatic rise in Muslims prisoners, 18% in 2021 compared with 8% in 2002.",
        "background": "We urge the Government to launch an independent review into racial inequalities in the criminal justice system, including:\r\n \r\n\u2022 Unwarranted arrests\r\n\u2022 Stop & search\r\n\u2022 Unfair outcomes from a civil/criminal judicial proceeding\r\n\u2022 Length of sentences\r\n\u2022 Deaths in custody",
